# seeds — environment configuration
#
# seeds does not read environment variables at runtime. This file exists
# so contributors know the convention applies: copy `.env.example` to
# `.env` if/when seeds starts reading env vars. `.env` itself is
# gitignored; `.env.example` is committed and tracked.
#
# Future-reserved keys (not yet read by any code path):
#
#   # SEEDS_DEBUG — when set, enable verbose internal diagnostics.
#   # SEEDS_DEBUG=
